explanation: "The arrow points to the posterior cruciate ligament attaching to posterior tibial condyle. ACL lies anteriorly, menisci are cartilaginous pads, and MCL is medial extracapsular.<br><br>**Signature Clues:**<br><br>* \u00a0**Location**: Posterior to ACL\n* \u00a0**Shape**: Thick, **C-shaped / curved band**\n* \u00a0**Signal**: Uniformly **low signal (dark)**\n* \u00a0**Attachment**: From tibia \u2192 medial femoral condyle\n<br><br><br>| **Ligament** | **Function** |\n| -------- | -------- |\n| **PCL** | Prevents posterior displacement of tibia |\n| ACL | Prevents anterior displacement |<br><br>\u00a0<br><br>| **Structure** | **Appearance** |\n| --------- | ---------- |\n| PCL | Thick, dark, curved |\n| ACL | Thin, oblique |\n| Meniscus | Triangular |\n| MCL | Linear (medial side) |",
