id: "1f22f3fb868d419d",
category: "Radiology",
subcategory: "01-general-radiology",
tags: ["ZVRecommended", "PYQ", "INI-CET May 2024"],
text: "Identify the correct statement:",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "CT uses non-filtered X-rays", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Radiation exposure in CT scan is 20mSv", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "CT is the initial investigation for gallstones", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "HU of water is zero", "is_correct": true}],
explanation: "The Hounsfield Unit (HU) of water is zero, serving as a reference point for measuring the radiodensity of various tissues in CT imaging.<br><br>X-rays pass through body\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\nDifferent tissues attenuate differently\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\nComputer assigns attenuation value\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\nStandardized as Hounsfield Units (HU)\n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 \u2193\nWater = 0 (reference point)<br><br>| **Substance** | **HU Value** |\n| --------- | -------- |\n| \u00a0Air | **-1000** |\n| \u00a0Fat | **-100 to -50** |\n| \u00a0**Water** | **0** \u2b50 |\n| \u00a0Soft tissue | +30 to +60 |\n| \u00a0Bone | +1000 |",
images: []
