text: "Which imaging modality is contraindicated in pregnancy?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "USG", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "MRI", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "CT", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "D", "text": "Doppler", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "CT uses ionizing radiation, harmful to fetus, hence contraindicated. **CT is contraindicated because-**<br><br>**Risks to fetus:**<br><br>* \u00a0DNA damage\n* \u00a0Congenital malformations\n* \u00a0Growth retardation\n* \u00a0Increased cancer risk later in life\n<br><br><br>Especially dangerous in: **First trimester**<br><br>USG, MRI, and Doppler are safe as they do not involve radiation.<br><br>| **Modality** | **Radiation** | **Safe in Pregnancy** |\n| -------- | --------- | ----------------- |\n| **USG** \u2b50 | \u274c No | \u2705 Safe |\n| **MRI** | \u274c No | \u2705 Safe (avoid contrast) |\n| **CT** | Yes | \u274c Avoid |\n| Doppler | \u274c No | \u2705 Safe |",
images: []
