explanation: "The pyriform sinuses appear as paired lateral air-filled recesses of the hypopharynx on AP neck X-rays, serving as important landmarks for foreign body detection and swallowing assessment.<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/4c4fa622-a9d0-4a03-ae1f-5e3ea2450252.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">\n**Signature Clues:**<br><br>* \u00a0**Air-filled space**\n* \u00a0**Lateral to larynx** (on both sides)\n* \u00a0Located in **hypopharynx**\n* Appears as a **triangular recess**",
images: [{"url": "https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/questions_image/01KN16PJC0AQKWC7S3RE8AFHA5.jpg", "caption": ""}]
